  "parent": "x-clade-west2792",
  "notes": "Standard Czech. Notable for the unique phoneme /r̝/ (⟨ř⟩) and systematic vowel length contrast. ⟨ch⟩ is the only official digraph and sorts as a separate letter. FINAL DEVOICING: obstruents devoice in coda/word-finally (b→p, d→t, ď→ť, g→k, v→f, z→s, ž→š, h→ch). H: voiced [ɦ] in onset; devoices to [x] in coda. Ě: [jɛ] after most consonants; causes palatal softening of preceding d/t/n. Sources: Palková (1994), Šimáčková et al. (2012), Short (1993).",
  "quality": "research",
